@NttCAD please check my comment again. Before you answered I had already checked, that compilation of the projects does not change anything. But if you added the library project to the module path of the application project and not to the classpath of the project, then I can reproduce your observation.
If you really added the project to the module path, then this is not a NetBeans issue, but a misunderstand what the module path is and how it differs from the classpath.
@pedro-w did the right thing by sharing the project he created. Please do so too.

How do you run the annotation processor? Anything special there?

I couldn't reproduce it either, no exceptions even without the dependency.
```java
package dev.mbien.mavenproject1;

import com.google.auto.service.AutoService;

public class Mavenproject1 {
    
    public interface FooService {
        void foo(String message);
    }
    
    @AutoService(FooService.class)
    public class FooServiceProvider implements FooService {
        @Override public void foo(String message) { }
    }
}
```
```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    <groupId>dev.mbien</groupId>
    <artifactId>mavenproject1</artifactId>
    <version>0.1-SNAPSHOT</version>
    <packaging>jar</packaging>
    <dependencies>
        <!--
        <dependency>
            <groupId>com.google.auto.service</groupId>
            <artifactId>auto-service</artifactId>
            <version>1.1.1</version>
            <scope>compile</scope>
        </dependency>
        -->
    </dependencies>
    <properties>
        <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>
        <exec.mainClass>dev.mbien.mavenproject1.Mavenproject1</exec.mainClass>
        <maven.compiler.release>21</maven.compiler.release>
    </properties>
</project>
```

The file is just a (very) simple POJO. It happen on multiple different files, event simple ones.

